text.tspan: Comparison of median income (or consumption) in LIS and World Bank
This data is adjusted for inflation and for differences in the cost of living between countries.
Median income or expenditure per day (PIP)
Daily median equivalized disposable household income (LIS)
Source: Incomes across the Distribution Database (Nolan, Thewissen, Roser) in levels (2016); World Bank PIP
Note: PIP data is measured in international-$ at 2017 prices. It relates to either disposable income or expenditure per capita (exact definitions
vary). LIS data in addition adjusts for the size and composition of households.
